    "Guaranteed or even probabilistic bounds on an instance's influence would enable influence estimation to be applied in settings where more than a \"heuristic approximation\" is required (Hammoudeh & Lowd, 2023).",
    "Improved Scalability: Influence estimation is slow.",
    "Analyzing each training instance's influence on a single test instance can take several hours or more (Barshan et al., 2020; Kobayashi et al., 2020; Guo et al., 2021; Hammoudeh & Lowd, 2022).",
    "For influence estimation to be a practical tool, it must be at least an order of magnitude faster.",
    "Heuristic influence analysis speed-ups could prove very useful (Guo et al., 2021; Schioppa et al., 2022)."
